HEADWORD: Syphilization
<hw>Syph`i*li*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Inoculation with the syphilitic virus, especially when employed as
a preventive measure, like vaccination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syphilize</ent>⟦br⟧
